                    <MudText Align="Align.Center" Typo="Typo.h4">Qilan</MudText>
                </MudCardHeader>
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudText >
                        Qilan is a lesser known Java framework for developing n-tier applications using SQL databases such as MySQL and SQL Server.
                        It is good for moving data between applications and giving a quick demonstartion of what can be done with the data in 
                        a given database. It is a great solution for small projects but may not be the best for complex domain logic. You don't
                        get the benefit of abstracting away the database as you would in a Spring application. Not that you cannot make a complex app, 
                        but it can lead to an extremely coupled system.
                    </MudText>
                    <br />
                    <MudText>
                        I am currently supporting an Electronic Health Record system and an inventory/CRM written solely with Qilan. If you're 
                        interested in how your organization could benefit from Qilan, please contact us.
                    </MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
                <MudCardActions>
                    <MudButton Class="float-right" Href="/contact" Color="Color.Primary">Contact us</MudButton>
                </MudCardActions>
            </MudCard>
