                        Most businesses today have two or more software products that are integral to business operations. 
                        A lot of these systems will rely on similar data and because re-entering data takes time and can introduce 
                        errors both of which can be very costly software companies have been building integrations into their products.
                        Integrations can be a very low such as Power BI or a webhook that triggers some event in the integrated app.
                        It can be cumbersome to piece together the right integrations and create a truly unified system with no low 
                        code integrations. Organizations should leverage the power of their software products available APIs to 
                        develop custom middleware between systems. This can lead to more coherent data model and allow executives to
                        see the big picture. 
